s://doi.org/10.1007/s00709-015-0858-6)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nReview\n\n# p24 family proteins: key players in the regulation of trafficking along the secretory pathway\n\nNoelia Pastor-Cantizano et al. Protoplasma. 2016 Jul.\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nProtoplasma\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Protoplasma%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Protoplasma%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2016 Jul;253(4):967-85.\n\ndoi: 10.1007/s00709-015-0858-6. Epub 2015 Jul 30.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Noelia Pastor-Cantizano](/?term=Pastor-Cantizano+N&cauthor_id=26224213)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain.\") , [Juan Carlos Montesinos](/?term=Montesinos+JC&cauthor_id=26224213)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain.\") , [César Bernat-Silvestre](/?term=Bernat-Silvestre+C&cauthor_id=26224213)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain.\") , [María Jesús Marcote](/?term=Marcote+MJ&cauthor_id=26224213)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain.\") , [Fernando Aniento](/?term=Aniento+F&cauthor_id=26224213)  [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain. Fernando.aniento@uv.es.\")\n\n### Affiliations\n\n-   1 Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain.\n-   2 Departamento de Bioquímica y Biología Molecular, Facultad de Farmacia, Universitat de València, Avenida Vicente Andrés Estellés, s/n, E-46100, Burjassot, Valencia, Spain. Fernando.aniento@uv.es.\n\n-   PMID: **26224213**\n-   DOI: [10.1007/s00709-015-0858-6](https://doi.org/10.1007/s00709-015-0858-6)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\np24 family proteins have been known for a long time, but their functions have remained elusive. However, they are emerging as essential regulators of protein trafficking along the secretory pathway, influencing the composition, structure, and function of different organelles in the pathway, especially the ER and the Golgi apparatus. In addition, they appear to modulate the transport of specific cargos, including GPI-anchored proteins, G-protein-coupled receptors, or K/HDEL ligands. As a consequence, they have been shown to play specific roles in signaling, development, insulin secretion, and the pathogenesis of Alzheimer's disease. The search of new putative ligands may open the way to discover new functions for this fascinating family of proteins.\n\n**Keywords:** COPI- and COPII-coated vesicles; Secretory pathway; p24 protein.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## References\n\n1.  1.  Nat Rev Microbiol. 2010 Jan;8(1):8-14 - [PubMed](/19946286/)\n2.  1.  Curr Opin Neurobiol. 2004 Jun;14(3):379-83 - [PubMed](/15194119/)\n3.  1.  J Cell Biol. 2010 Nov 1;191(3):479-92 - [PubMed](/21041443/)\n4.  1.  J Biol Chem. 2009 Oct 16;284(42):28634-41 - [PubMed](/19710022/)\n5.  1.  J Biol Chem. 1996 Oct 25;271(43):26939-46 - [PubMed](/8900179/)\n\nShow all 126 references\n\n## Public