{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778378617787,"sessionID":"ses_1f0683152ffeCYT9xjnCqVwnXn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_du3hVps86rvFTixidrocUMn0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes: p24 Cargo Receptor Complex\n+\n+## Relevant GO Pattern\n+\n+`src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml` defines protein complex terms by a molecular function:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of <molecular function>\n+```\n+\n+The requested parent term already follows the relevant pattern:\n+\n+```obo\n+id: GO:0062137\n+name: cargo receptor complex\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of GO:0038024 ! cargo receptor activity\n+intersection_of: part_of GO:0016020 ! membrane\n+```\n+\n+## Existing Precedent\n+\n+`GO:0061852 retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER` is an asserted child of `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` and adds a process capability relation:\n+\n+```obo\n+is_a: GO:0062137 ! cargo receptor complex\n+relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0006890 ! retrograde vesicle-mediated transport, Golgi to endoplasmic reticulum\n+```\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+The new p24 term is a specific named cargo receptor complex. It should be asserted as an `is_a` child of `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` and may include a `capable_of_part_of` relation to `GO:0090110 COPII-coated vesicle cargo loading`, matching existing cargo receptor complex precedent.\n+\n+No new `intersection_of` logical definition is added. The parent already captures the general cargo receptor complex pattern, while asserting an equivalence for the p24-specific complex based on ER exit or COPII cargo loading would over-specify the term.\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+# Research Notes: p24 Cargo Receptor Complex\n+\n+## PMID:34647572 \"Differential use of p24 family members as cargo receptors for the transport of glycosylphosphatidylinositol-anchored proteins and Wnt1.\"\n+\n+This article supports that p24 proteins form complexes that act as cargo receptors for COPII-mediated transport from the ER and that p24 complexes include members of all four p24 subfamilies.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34647572 \"Complexes of p24 proteins act as cargo receptors for the transport of COPII vesicles from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER).\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34647572 \"The major cargos of p24 complexes are hydrophilic proteins tethered to the ER membrane via a covalently attached glycosylphosphatidylinositol (GPI) or fatty acid.\"\n+\n+## PMID:27569046 \"3D Structure and Interaction of p24beta and p24delta Golgi Dynamics Domains: Implication for p24 Complex Formation and Cargo Transport.\"\n+\n+This article supports p24 hetero-oligomeric complex formation and its role in efficient cargo transport from the ER to the Golgi apparatus.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:27569046 \"We propose that the heterophilic interaction of p24 GOLD domains contributes to the formation of the p24 hetero-oligomeric complex and to efficient cargo transport.\"\n+\n+## PMID:19566487 \"The p24 family and selective transport processes at the ER-Golgi interface.\"\n+\n+This review supports the role of p24 proteins in selective ER-Golgi transport and interactions with COPI and COPII coat complexes.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19566487 \"One of the key processes in the secretory pathway concerns the transport of cargo proteins from the ER (endoplasmic reticulum) to the Golgi.\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19566487 \"These p24 proteins are thought to play an important role in the selective transport processes at the ER-Golgi interface, although their exact functioning is still obscure.\"\n+\n+## PMID:26224213 \"p24 family proteins: key players in the regulation of trafficking along the secretory pathway.\"\n+\n+This review supports that p24 family proteins regulate trafficking along the secretory pathway and modulate transport of specific cargo, including GPI-anchored proteins.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26224213 \"p24 family proteins have been known for a long time, but their functions have remained elusive.\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26224213 \"In addition, they appear to modulate the transport of specific cargos, including GPI-anchored proteins, G-protein-coupled receptors, or K/HDEL ligands.\"\n+\n+## PMID:32456004 \"Dual Independent Roles of the p24 Complex in Selectivity of Secretory Cargo Export from the Endoplasmic Reticulum\"\n+\n+PubMed page validation confirmed the PMID, title, DOI 10.3390/cells9051295, and abstract. NCBI cache validation via `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:32456004` was blocked by HTTP 429 rate limiting during this run. The PubMed abstract supports that the p24 protein complex acts as a specific cargo receptor for GPI-anchored proteins and facilitates ER exit in yeast.\n+\n+## Reference Validation\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference` succeeded for PMID:34647572, PMID:27569046, PMID:19566487, and PMID:26224213. PMID:32456004 was validated manually from PubMed because automated caching was rate-limited.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes: p24 Cargo Receptor Complex\n+\n+## Relevant GO Pattern\n+\n+`src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml` defines protein complex terms by a molecular function:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of <molecular function>\n+```\n+\n+The requested parent term already follows the relevant pattern:\n+\n+```obo\n+id: GO:0062137\n+name: cargo receptor complex\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of GO:0038024 ! cargo receptor activity\n+intersection_of: part_of GO:0016020 ! membrane\n+```\n+\n+## Existing Precedent\n+\n+`GO:0061852 retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER` is an asserted child of `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` and adds a process capability relation:\n+\n+```obo\n+is_a: GO:0062137 ! cargo receptor complex\n+relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0006890 ! retrograde vesicle-mediated transport, Golgi to endoplasmic reticulum\n+```\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+The new p24 term is a specific named cargo receptor complex. It should be asserted as an `is_a` child of `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` and may include a `capable_of_part_of` relation to `GO:0090110 COPII-coated vesicle cargo loading`, matching existing cargo receptor complex precedent.\n+\n+No new `intersection_of` logical definition is added. The parent already captures the general cargo receptor complex pattern, while asserting an equivalence for the p24-specific complex based on ER exit or COPII cargo loading would over-specify the term.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+# Research Notes: p24 Cargo Receptor Complex\n+\n+## PMID:34647572 \"Differential use of p24 family members as cargo receptors for the transport of glycosylphosphatidylinositol-anchored proteins and Wnt1.\"\n+\n+This article supports that p24 proteins form complexes that act as cargo receptors for COPII-mediated transport from the ER and that p24 complexes include members of all four p24 subfamilies.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34647572 \"Complexes of p24 proteins act as cargo receptors for the transport of COPII vesicles from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER).\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34647572 \"The maj